"O - I've been patiently waiting for this beer since I heard they were making it. I'm a sucker for mango, big wheat beers, and Weyerbacher. I wasn't let down. I very much appreciated the sour flavors present here. I would have liked a little bit more mango flavor. Another great beer from this imperial anniversary series."
"Pours a hazy amber with a thick but fizzy white head, a few sprays of lace on the glass. Smell: pale sweetness and wheat cracker, dried mango and other soft fruit... a swirl and there's a vaguely banana pudding thing, then it's gone and just a pale wheat w/ sweetened dried mango. Taste: out of nowhere this is tart... lactic... which is good because otherwise it would be just cloying undercarbonated pale malt overload. Sugary mango again, then tart jolly rancher finish. Sticky. Sneakily boozy post swallow. This is rough but there's one point in the sip where it's an interesting idea...then a sugar wave hits and it's rough again. Get rid of the ""anniversary beers are >10%"" motto and try this again?"
